HEADWORD: Avocado
<hw>Av`o*ca"do</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted
from the Mexican <ets>ahuacatl</ets>: cf. Sp. <ets>aguacate</ets>, F.
<ets>aguacat⟦eacute⟧</ets>, <ets>avocat</ets>, G.
<ets>avogado</ets>baum.]</ety> <def>The pulpy fruit of <spn>Persea
gratissima</spn>, a tree of tropical America. It is about the size and
shape of a large pear; -- called also <altname>avocado pear</altname>,
<altname>alligator pear</altname>, <altname>midshipman's
butter</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

